snippet.textDisplay: This isn't bad at all. In fact, it's quite nice, soothing and has a fresh feel to it. And yes, I am writing this after having heard and enjoyed most of the previous CSP seasons over the years. People should seriously try to loosen up sometimes and appreciate the hard work and creativity that goes into coming up with each and every piece of this wonderful phenomenon called CSP. At least, there's a genuine effort being put to preserve the old traditions, cultures and the beauty of our classical music, and infuse it with contemporary style to create something that appeals to a wide range of audiences. As an Indian Canadian, I feel nothing but immense love, respect and a weird sense of happiness every time I listen to any production from the house of CSP. Much love..
